# Herdr reboot triage report

Flagg rebooted. The herdr session came back with 59 panes across 37 workspaces. Five pi workers investigated every workspace against session transcripts, repo state, and Brain briefs. Full evidence lives in the five `triage-*.svx` assets beside this report. This report is the operator surface: verdicts, what needs you, and a continuation prompt for every thread worth resuming.

## The numbers

| Verdict | Count | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| SHIPPED | 15 | Work landed with commit receipts. Panes are trophies; janitor may close. |
| BLOCKED-ON-JOEL | 11 | Waiting on a decision, password, or artifact only you can supply. |
| ACTIVE | 6 | Live sessions, coherent. Left alone. |
| INTERESTING | 4 | Interrupted mid-flight with uncommitted work at risk. |
| ABANDONED | 1 | Discord bridge — deliberately killed after e2e (commit `09f97de`). |

