These four have real diffs sitting in working trees. Each block below is a complete prompt for a fresh session.

### 1. Egghead commerce: harvest the four research lanes (w6)

```text
Objective
Resume the Move Egghead Commerce to CourseBuilder charter. Harvest the four completed research lanes into the shared brief, reconcile their evidence, and continue toward the v1 contract and cutover design. CourseBuilder must become the sole commerce writer without rebuilding existing Stripe objects.

State
The brief landed in commit 41b9c8b at .brain/projects/egghead-commerce/egghead-commerce-brief.svx. Four workers completed read-only research and left uncommitted assets in separate worktrees:
- /Users/joel/Code/worktrees/migrate-egghead-commerce-rails/.brain/projects/egghead-commerce/asset-rails-commerce-surfaces.svx
- /Users/joel/Code/worktrees/migrate-egghead-commerce-coursebuilder/.brain/projects/egghead-commerce/asset-coursebuilder-commerce-capabilities.svx
- /Users/joel/Code/worktrees/migrate-egghead-commerce-slack/.brain/projects/egghead-commerce/asset-slack-commerce-context.svx
- /Users/joel/Code/worktrees/migrate-egghead-commerce-stripe/.brain/projects/egghead-commerce/asset-stripe-object-event-inventory.svx
Each matching step file is modified and closed in its worktree. No research commit was created. The Stripe lane found 7,541 unique events over 90 days and 2,875 errored or processing events, mostly invoice.payment_failed.

Resume points
- pi --session /Users/joel/.pi/agent/sessions/--Users-joel-Code-skillrecordings-migrate-egghead--/2026-07-17T18-33-25-526Z_019f715a-d316-7281-a7ef-1f12c6e2b546.jsonl
- /Users/joel/Code/skillrecordings/migrate-egghead/.brain/projects/egghead-commerce/egghead-commerce-brief.svx
- The four worktrees and asset paths listed above

Next steps
1. Review each asset and matching closed step.
2. Copy or reconcile the accepted files into the main migrate-egghead checkout without losing worktree changes.
3. Add concise decision-ledger entries to the shared brief.
4. Run pi-notes brain check and inspect the exact diff.
5. Continue with grill-commerce-v1-contract.svx and grill-cutover-sequence-and-gates.svx before implementation slices.

Gotchas
- Existing Stripe customers, subscriptions, products, and prices stay in place.
- Rails is still the commerce/access writer. Do not change production writer ownership without Joel's explicit gate.
- CourseBuilder 3.x has reusable checkout and workflow machinery, but the survey found missing webhook await/dedupe safety, subscription lifecycle, atomic seats/entitlements, and reconciliation.
- Keep customer data, Stripe identifiers, tokens, and raw Slack history out of Brain artifacts.
```

